===Adjective===
'''irregardless'''

# ''(non-standard):'' [[regardless]].

====Usage Note====
This term is often cited as redundant, incorrect, or not a proper word at all.  Alternately, the synonym ''regardless'' appears to be about 200 times more common on the web and is unlikely to provoke controversy over usage.

Anal-retentive types, or English majors, may try to correct your usage of this word.  If confronted by this type you have four options.  1: Ignore them.  2: Remind them that "irregardless" is found in the Oxford English Dictionary, and is now considered to be a valid word.  3: Point out that you don't throw a fit when they use words like "debone" or "unravel".  4: Punch them in the face.  English Majors and Anal-Retentive types rarely know how to put up a good fight and tend to go down crying after one hit.

